<subSubSection id="997191D0ABA28CA843A7B1274FBD725A" pageId="0" pageNumber="113" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="BD3C7626AAE90B335265C49B58B269E4" pageId="0" pageNumber="113">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="92D367CB20D46F10A7E7F156F46650DF" pageId="0" pageNumber="113">
The species epithet, 
<taxonomicName id="4A0F4E1D73E961FC652459A39B59C776" authority="Konstantinov &amp; Linzmeier, 2020" authorityName="Konstantinov &amp; Linzmeier" authorityYear="2020" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Erinaceialtica" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="thomasi" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="113" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="thomasi">thomasi</taxonomicName>
, is a patronym in honor of late Mike Thomas, who contributed greatly to our knowledge of beetle diversity, taxonomy, and identification in the United States.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
